Hay guys,
I am a new user of Cantera for a couple of days and I am fascinating 
by what you can do with it for free. I have read that there should 
come out a new version of cantera in January by which you can 
calculate the 1-D adiabatic laminar flame speed with Matlab and 
Python, similar to what the PREMIX-package can do in CHEMKIN. Does 
anybody knows when this version will be posted?
Another question I have is about the spherical transient 1-d flame 
speed calculation under constant volume conditions.
Is there maybe someone who has planed or already has written a code 
for that kind of problem? Or is it maybe planed in the future to 
implement this in Cantera?
Thank you very much in advance for an answer.

Best regards
Sven
